24.30	The_Last_Station	The Last Station	The Last Station is a 2009 biographical drama film directed by Michael Hoffman. It is an adaptation of the 1990 biographical novel of the same name by Jay Parini about the final months of Leo Tolstoy's life. The film stars Christopher Plummer as Tolstoy and Helen Mirren as his wife Sophia Tolstaya. The film is about the battle between Sophia and his disciple Vladimir Chertkov for his legacy and the copyright of his works. The film premiered at the 2009 Telluride Film Festival.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/85/Last_stationposter1.jpg/220px-Last_stationposter1.jpg
